To evaluate \(x - \frac{3}{8}\) at \(x = -\frac{5}{2}\), first write both terms with denominator 8:

\[
-\frac{5}{2} \;=\;-\frac{5\cdot 4}{2\cdot 4}\;=\;- \frac{20}{8}.
\]

Then
\[
-\frac{5}{2}\;-\;\frac{3}{8}
\;=\;
-\frac{20}{8}\;-\;\frac{3}{8}
\;=\;
-\frac{23}{8}.
\]

Answer: \(-\tfrac{23}{8}\).
